The article is a transcript of remarks made by NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg and US Vice President Mike Pence at a press conference. Stoltenberg emphasized the importance of the transatlantic bond between the United States and Europe, and expressed gratitude for the US' commitment to the security of Europe. He also discussed the progress made in the fight against terrorism and the need for higher defense spending among NATO members. Pence reiterated the US' support for NATO and its commitment to increasing military funding. He also addressed concerns about the dismissal of General Flynn and assured that the US values the freedom of the press.